      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:2:74:17",
      "text": [
        " لَا يُلَاعِنُ الرَّجُلُ الْمَرْأَةَ الَّتِي يَتَمَتَّعُ بِهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad, from Ahmad, from Ibn Mahboub, from Al A’ala Bin Razeyn, from Ibn Abu Yafour, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The man cannot curse the woman which he is temporarily married with’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "17. Muhammad ibn Ahmad has narrated from ibn Mahbub from al-‘Ala’ ibn Razin from ibn abu Ya‘fur who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘A man cannot go through the process of al-Li‘an (condemnation) against his wife in the manner of Mut‘ah (advantageous marriage).”’ "
        ]
      }
